title: Rebel Wilson models own fashion collection
text:
Rebel Wilson unveils her new fashion line as Julie Bishop commits to investing in Australian fashion Melissa Hoyer news.com.au Rebel Wilson unveils her new fashion line as Julie Bishop commits to investing in Australian fashion Melissa Hoyer news.com.au Actress, writer and comedienne Rebel Wilson. Picture: AP 
LOS Angeles was buzzing with Aussie excitement last night as both the actor Rebel Wilson and Foreign Minister Julie Bishop announced their commitment to the big wide world of fashion. 
The clever Rebel Wilson, who was on the arm of Australian actor Hugh Sheridan at the Aussie fashion showcase, as part of LA fashion week, told news.com.au that her fashion line, Rebel Wilson for Torrid was also unveiled - and cleverly worn on herself. 
She drew the line at actually getting up there on the runway, preferring to wear it on the comfort of the red carpet. Melissa Hoyer with Rebel Wilson Rebel with Hugh Sheridan Melissa chats with Australia’s Julie Bishop. Ms Bishop gave up a few inches on the carpet. Julie Bishop, Rebel Wilson and Hugh Sheridan Source: INSTAGRAM Hugh, Rebel and Julie. 1 of n 
“My label is called Rebel Wilson for Torrid (a plus-size fashion line), so hopefully people won’t get it confused with Rebel Sport,” said the comedic actor. 
“It’s actually been really fun to design to be honest and it goes on sale in three weeks. 
“And as a special deal to all Australians I’m going to give you 50% off for shipping, so isn’t that a great deal!” Other Stories
